<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-82] MarkerFilter causes Markers to be incorrectly created. SLF4J Markers cause ClassCastException</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-82</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;MarkerFilter calls MarkerManager.getMarker().  This will cause the Marker to be created when the configuration is processed and generally won&apos;t allow the application to create the Markers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;MarkerWrapper&apos;s instanceOf method tries to cast a Marker to a MarkerWrapper even when the Marker is not a MarkerWrapper, causing a ClassCastException.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
